body:
Yes, it is a problem on php 8. Untill we fix it please don't use `NumberFormatter::GROUPING_SEPARATOR_SYMBOL => '_'` the way you did. Instead you can set it like:

    Yii::$app->formatter->thousandSeparator = '_';

or

    Yii::$app->formatter->numberFormatterSymbols[NumberFormatter::GROUPING_SEPARATOR_SYMBOL] = '_';

If I use `NumberFormatter::GROUPING_SEPARATOR_SYMBOL => '_'` in `$textOptions` instead of `$options` I don't get the desired result. The currency symbol get changed instead of the thousands separator.

This works:

    Yii::$app->formatter->thousandSeparator = '_';

But this doesn't:

    Yii::$app->formatter->numberFormatterSymbols[NumberFormatter::GROUPING_SEPARATOR_SYMBOL] = '_';
